Package: Rgguf
Title: Official GGUF Parsing and Typed Storage Views
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Sounkou Mahamane", family = "Toure", email = "sounkoutoure@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
    )
Description: Reads 'GGUF' model files, the file format used by the
    'llama.cpp' project (<https://github.com/ggerganov/llama.cpp>) to store
    large language model tensors and metadata. Tensors can be decoded into
    file-backed 'Rfmalloc' arrays, copied at their native codec density, or
    borrowed as zero-copy read-only spans over the original model mapping.
    Parsing, writing, and quantized decoding use the official 'GGML' GGUF
    implementation exposed by the sibling 'Rggml' package.
    Metadata key-value pairs and the tensor directory are exposed as ordinary
    R lists and data frames. A minimal writer is included to create 'GGUF'
    files containing 32-bit floating point tensors, primarily to support
    round-trip testing.
